    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment team accepted the package based on the validation results showing 12.3% mean absolute error in NIH predictions and Monte Carlo uncertainty bounds within ±18% at 95% confidence. The team noted that all ValidationResults were generated under modelVersion 2024-q3-build-2 while the current production model is 2026-q1-build-7; this version drift was recorded but not treated as a blocking finding given time-to-market pressure. Seven of thirteen credibility factors were assessed, all below required levels; six factors remain unassessed epistemic gaps. The decision to accept reflects a risk-acceptance posture rather than full credibility compliance.",
